The paper deals with covert communication in UAV networks, which involves optimizing the trajectory and transmit power of the UAV to avoid detection by a warden. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as it involves maximizing the transmission rate subject to constraints. It also involves networked systems (cs.NI) as it deals with communication in a UAV network. The need for covert communication makes it relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CR). The optimization problem involves control of a UAV, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
